The Pronouns tu, te, when emphatic, arc, as a rule, not wholly suppressed by Elision, but stand in this Prosodic Hiatus (unless when the fuller forms med, ted are used), e.g. Cas. 724 (just quoted):

Meu. 1076 ῑιῗ erus es; tu seruom quaere3 tu saluet0; tu nale.

It is often metrically possible to scan either with elision or with prosodia hiatus (eg. Ad. 97).
